@host = http://localhost:3000

# Replace <TOKEN> with the JWT from `auth.http` login response.

### List tasks (paginated)
GET {{host}}/api/tasks
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

### Create a task
POST {{host}}/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

{
  "title": "Buy milk",
  "description": "From the supermarket"
}

### Get a single task (replace :id)
GET {{host}}/api/tasks/:id
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

### Update a task (replace :id)
PUT {{host}}/api/tasks/:id
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

{
  "completed": true
}

### Delete a task (replace :id)
DELETE {{host}}/api/tasks/:id
Authorization: Bearer <TOKEN>

# Tips:
# - When using VS Code REST Client: after login, copy the `token` value and paste into `Authorization` header as `Bearer <token>`.
# - Use query params like `?page=1&limit=10&q=search&completed=true&sort=-createdAt` for listing.
